    id: 476,
    date: "2024-01-12T16:19:07",
    date_gmt: "2024-01-12T16:19:07",
    guid: { rendered: "http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/?p=476" },
    modified: "2024-01-12T16:19:07",
    modified_gmt: "2024-01-12T16:19:07",
    slug: "thee-khai-aehm-parrier-2022",
    status: "publish",
    type: "post",
    link: "https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/thee-khai-aehm-parrier-2022/",
    title: { rendered: "Thee Khai Aehm, &#8220;Parrier&#8221; (2022)" },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>Combining classic noisy dirty fun of The Cramps and Butthole Surfers with video games like Diablo and Dark Souls plus some Lord of the Rings and Dungeons &amp; Dragons, Thee Khai Aehm\u2019s <em>Parrier </em>reappropriates the past while adding strictly modern nerdy flair.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The EP begins with guttural noises and faint Gregorian-style chanting of \u201cGrave Wraith\u201d before descending into A-grade garage-infused horror. It\u2019s where the aforementioned The Cramps influence becomes clear without ever sounding like a mere tribute.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cTribok Travelling\u201d is sheer fun with it\u2019s fast tempos, skeleton-dancing guitar and slightly off-key falsetto harmonies. Tribok is aka trebuchet.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio embed-youtube"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe loading="lazy" title="THEE KHAI AEHM - Tribok Travelling (official visualizer)" width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/f9IeO4hLN84?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cImp\u201d is slow and sludgy with a wash of instruments only&nbsp; penetrated by a hypnotic tambourine. You\u2019d die in a mosh to this.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cWhole Once More\u201d slightly picks up the tempo while continuing the trance-like repetitiveness of its predecessor. The interplay of distant vocals could send chill down the spine if listened to alone in a dark alley (speaking from experience here).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio embed-youtube"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe loading="lazy" title="THEE KHAI AEHM - Whole Once More (official visualizer)" width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/t1ytIJI0Qh8?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cEvens Up\u201d is 60s garage freakiness at its best. <a href="https://oddboll.net/home/premiere-thee-khai-aehm-evens-up">As we mentioned before</a>, this <em>is</em> the sound of summer.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By the time \u201cThe Gathering at Mocking Tower\u201d starts, we\u2019re back to driving tempos. With chord progression referencing the very best of proto-punk you\u2019d be pressed not to nod along.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Parrier</em> is sheer noisy horror fun and one of the most true to its roots releases we\u2019ve heard recently.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<iframe style="border: 0; width: 100%; height: 120px;" src="https://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/album=3549358310/size=large/bgcol=333333/linkcol=e99708/tracklist=false/artwork=small/transparent=true/" seamless><a href="https://theekhaiaehm.bandcamp.com/album/parrier">Parrier by THEE KHAI AEHM</a></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: {
      rendered:
        "<p>Horror garage rockers are back with the second release this year</p>\n",
      protected: false,
    },
