    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>Ahead of the release of <a href="https://theekhaiaehm.bandcamp.com/album/parrier">Thee Khai Aehm\u2019s</a>&nbsp;<em>Parrier</em> EP this Saturday (save the date, yo), check out their new track \u201cEvens Up\u201d.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>According to Paul (y\u2019know, from the band), the tracks on <em>Parrier</em> were inspired by video games, movies and RPGs like Dark Souls, Diablo, DND and Lord of the Rings. <em>Tolkiencore</em>, anybody?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The evergreen garage progressions from the 60s hark back to the best of freakbeat as well as The Cramps. At the same time, the track packs a strictly modern punch. The chants in breakdowns are destined to be crowd-pleasers during shows.<br><br>Tasty overloaded guitars, sizzling cymbals, vocals drenched in oldschool echo \u2014 this <em>is</em> the sound of summer, iykwim.</p>\n\n\n\n<iframe style="border: 0; width: 100%; height: 120px;" src="https://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/album=3549358310/size=large/bgcol=333333/linkcol=e99708/tracklist=false/artwork=small/track=395273389/transparent=true/" seamless><a href="https://theekhaiaehm.bandcamp.com/album/parrier">Parrier by THEE KHAI AEHM</a></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: {
      rendered: "<p>Noisy garage from tireless German noisers</p>\n",
      protected: false,
    },
