    id: 469,
    date: "2024-01-12T16:13:07",
    date_gmt: "2024-01-12T16:13:07",
    guid: { rendered: "http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/?p=469" },
    modified: "2024-01-12T16:13:30",
    modified_gmt: "2024-01-12T16:13:30",
    slug: "otoboke-beaver-super-champon-2022",
    status: "publish",
    type: "post",
    link: "https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/otoboke-beaver-super-champon-2022/",
    title: { rendered: "Otoboke Beaver, \u201cSuper Champon\u201d (2022)" },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>You\u2019d think that after nearly 50 years a genre would eventually die out <em>*wind is drying tears as \u201cWhat A Fool Believes\u201d is playing in the distance*</em>. But somehow punk is still not dead (yeah, we said it) and every decade manages to reimagine and repurpose the genre. And give us lots of exciting bands to listen to.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Otoboke Beaver are probably more punk than many \u201cclassic\u201d punk bands. Both musically and content-wise.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1705075940782_80"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="760" height="507" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/otoboke-beaver-bad-luck-premiere.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-471" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/otoboke-beaver-bad-luck-premiere.jpeg 760w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/otoboke-beaver-bad-luck-premiere-300x200.jpeg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em>Super Champions</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Musically, <em>Super Champon</em> takes the best from the last 50 years of punk rock and exaggerates it to cartoonish extremes. Breakneck tempos that change several times during the course of one track and sound like a stream of consciousness. 18 songs in 21 minutes. Several of them under 20 seconds. Riot grrrl themes. Fuck yeah!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The bans called this album a \u201cmasterpiece of chaos music\u201d and we couldn\u2019t agree more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Super Champon</em> is to be enjoyed in its entirety. Just be careful if you decide to bang your head to it.</p>\n\n\n\n<iframe style="border: 0; width: 100%; height: 120px;" src="https://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/album=1933178362/size=large/bgcol=ffffff/linkcol=de270f/tracklist=false/artwork=small/transparent=true/" seamless><a href="https://music.otobokebeaver.com/album/super-champon">SUPER CHAMPON \u30b9\u30fc\u30d1\u30fc\u30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30dd\u30f3 by Otoboke Beaver \u304a\u3068\u307c\u3051\u30d3\uff5e\u30d0\uff5e</a></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: {
      rendered:
        "<p>Evergreen punk frenzy proves the undying relevance of the genre</p>\n",
      protected: false,
    },
