    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>Hey hey!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We\u2019ve got exciting news to share! Check out our new show on <a href="https://fsr.live/">fsr.live</a>!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This one was a mixed bag of different stuff we\u2019re into and we promise to deliver more of this goodness every third Monday of the month\ud83d\udda4</p>\n\n\n\n<iframe loading="lazy" width="100%" height="120" src="https://player-widget.mixcloud.com/widget/iframe/?hide_cover=1&#038;feed=%2Ffsrlive%2Fodd-hour-18july2022%2F" frameborder="0" ></iframe>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Tracklist:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Karlheinz Stockhausen &#8211; Struktur VI<br>2. Einst\u00fcrzende Neubauten &#8211; Sado-Masodub<br>3. Mescalinum United &#8211; We Have Arrived (Aphex Twin QQT Mix)<br>4. Richard H. Kirk &#8211; Public Fun<br>5. Chris Clark &#8211; The Chase<br>6. Leila &#8211; Activate I<br>7. We Be Echo &#8211; Sexuality<br>8. Shuggie Otis &#8211; XL-30<br>9. Antipop Consortium &#8211; Ghostlawns<br>10. Danny Brown &#8211; Golddust<br>11. d\u00e4lek &#8211; Culture For Dollars<br>12. Big Black &#8211; Passing Complexion<br>13. Butthole Surfers &#8211; The O-Men<br>14. Pixies &#8211; Distance Equals Rate Times Time<br>15 .Germs &#8211; Forming<br>16. Grinderman &#8211; No Pussy Blues<br>17. Billy Bragg &#8211; There Is Power In A Union<br>18. Coil &#8211; Lorca not Orca<br>19. John Zorn &#8211; Rejoicing<br>20. Ornette Coleman &#8211; Lonely Woman<br>21. John Coltrane &#8211; Jupiter<br>22. Ornette Coleman &#8211; First Take<br>23. Ornette Coleman &#8211; The Good Life</p>\n\n\n\n<p>24. Station ID<br>25. Barry Adamson &#8211; Something Wicked This Way Comes</p>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
