    title: { rendered: "Danny Brown, \u201cAtrocity Exhibition\u201d (2016)" },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>Not even 5 seconds into \u201cDownward Spiral\u201d, the opening track from Danny Brown\u2019s impeccable fourth album, things are already weird. Uneven beat, double bass and Brown\u2019s distinct delivery sound refreshingly different.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Produced primarily by <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paul_White_(record_producer)">Paul White</a>, the beats borrow from unusual sources ranging from free jazz to New Order-inspired bass lines. But what else would you expect from a hip hop album named after a Joy Division song? The production is dark, lofi and claustrophobic. For the whole 47 minutes there\u2019s a persisting sense of dread and unease.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1705011824957_81"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="955" height="535" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/2016_dannybrown_Saccenti_280916.hero_.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-386" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/2016_dannybrown_Saccenti_280916.hero_.jpg 955w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/2016_dannybrown_Saccenti_280916.hero_-300x168.jpg 300w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/2016_dannybrown_Saccenti_280916.hero_-768x430.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 955px) 100vw, 955px" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But the beats are not the way they are on their own. The crippling dark atmosphere of this record only exists to compliment Brown\u2019s lyrics and delivery. As aptly summarized by (god forbid) <a href="https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/review-danny-browns-atrocity-exhibition-is-an-awesome-bummed-out-party-104845/">Rolling Stone</a>: \u201c[<em>Atrocity Exhibition</em>] is the year\u2019s most thrilling cry for help\u201d.<br>Brown\u2019s rhymes and flow are rooted in the old school. The wordplay has a prominent place here with rhymes like: \u201cMimosa for breakfast/With a thick ho from Texas\u201d and \u201cRocks about the size as the teeth in Chris Rock\u2019s mouth.\u201d\u00a0</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio embed-youtube"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe loading="lazy" title="Danny Brown - Ain&#039;t It Funny (Official Video, dir. Jonah Hill)" width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/7L4JnAuW00k?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Atrocity Exhibition </em>is groundbreaking in terms of being at the same time relatively mainstream and completely fucked up. It\u2019s Danny Brown on top of his game.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<iframe style="border: 0; width: 100%; height: 120px;" src="https://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/album=1940212110/size=large/bgcol=333333/linkcol=ffffff/tracklist=false/artwork=small/transparent=true/" seamless><a href="https://dannybrown.bandcamp.com/album/atrocity-exhibition">Atrocity Exhibition by Danny Brown</a></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: {
      rendered:
        "<p>One of the most idiosyncratic hip hop albums of the decade</p>\n",
      protected: false,
    },
