    modified_gmt: "2024-01-11T22:20:20",
    slug: "anti-pop-consortium-arrythmia-2002",
    status: "publish",
    type: "post",
    link: "https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/anti-pop-consortium-arrythmia-2002/",
    title: { rendered: "Anti-Pop Consortium, \u201cArrythmia\u201d (2002)" },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>With hip hop being a prevalent force in music these days it makes it harder and harder to do something truly unique. Let alone being able to hold the title for almost 20 years.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Arrythmia</em>\u2019s album title is a rare example of a perfectly captured essence of the content. The beats, even though rooted in the hip hop tradition of the day, are never conventional. The lyrics are futuristic, weird and smart. After all two of the three MCs come from the ever-rewarding New York street poetry scene. Flawlessly mixing hip hop and IDM, it\u2019s not surprising that after a series of releases on their own Antipop Recordings, Anti-Pop Consortium got the attention of <a href="https://warp.net/">WARP records</a> known for releasing such behemoths as Aphex Twin, Autechre and Boards Of Canada.\u00a0</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio embed-youtube"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe loading="lazy" title="Antipop Consortium - Ghostlawns" width="500" height="375" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Zjp2HUY7dQY?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>First thing you notice when putting on <em>Arrythmia</em> is the production. The beats drip intelligent weirdness bordering on brainy but never succumbing to the inaccessible. The sheer weirdness of the ideas that went into those beats are worthy of Sun Ra, who the band cite as a major influence. Contrary to the prevalent production methods of most hip hop of the era (and arguably even now) APC meticulously sculpt their drums from scratch without relying on dusty vinyl. The samples they utilize are following the drums closely in their unlikeliness: you can find chirping crickets, robotic video game bleeps, bubbling sounds, and \u2014 a highlight of hip hop production weirdness \u2014 an entire beat built around the bouncing ping pong ball (guess which one?).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1705011530995_85"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1000" height="1000" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/anti-pop-consortium.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-376" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/anti-pop-consortium.jpeg 1000w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/anti-pop-consortium-300x300.jpeg 300w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/anti-pop-consortium-150x150.jpeg 150w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/anti-pop-consortium-768x768.jpeg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em>The expressions you make while listening to </em>Arrythmia \u00a9 <em>ninjatune.net</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Upon original release, <em>Arrythmia </em>received enthusiastic reviews that did not necessarily translate into sales. The album made some minor waves in NYC but overall failed to reach wider audiences.<br>BUT! While reviewing it in 2021 it\u2019s impossible to miss just how refreshingly <em>different</em> the album sounds today. So much has been done in music since its release but very few came close to such a successful mix of WARP-style IDM and hip hop. Despite electronic music being at arguably its most mainstream and inventive at the same time.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Probably best said by Apple Music: \u201cNo one else was doing this style of hip-hop in 2002, and no one has pulled it off since.\u201d</p>\n\n\n\n<iframe style="border: 0; width: 100%; height: 120px;" src="https://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/album=2203535680/size=large/bgcol=333333/linkcol=9a64ff/tracklist=false/artwork=small/transparent=true/" seamless><a href="https://warprecords.bandcamp.com/album/arrhythmia">Arrhythmia by Antipop Consortium</a></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: "<p>When WARP does hip hop</p>\n", protected: false },
