    id: 347,
    date: "2024-01-11T22:04:25",
    date_gmt: "2024-01-11T22:04:25",
    guid: { rendered: "http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/?p=347" },
    modified: "2024-01-11T22:07:33",
    modified_gmt: "2024-01-11T22:07:33",
    slug: "kotra-zavoloka-silence-2020",
    status: "publish",
    type: "post",
    link: "https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/kotra-zavoloka-silence-2020/",
    title: { rendered: "Kotra &amp; Zavoloka, \u201cSilence\u201d (2020)" },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>If you knew you had to close your label forever, what would be your final release?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Influential Ukrainian label <a href="https://kvitnu.com/">Kvitnu</a> solved this issue by doing something very them \u2014 released a 7\u201d of silence. No, seriously, the entire 7\u201d is just one locked groove with nothing but silence on it. Pretty cool, huh? Sure, <a href="https://youtu.be/JTEFKFiXSx4">John Cage</a> was there first but this release is different proving that you <em>can</em> make two different records of silence indeed. Again, very much what Kvitnu are all about.\u00a0</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio embed-youtube"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe loading="lazy" title="KOTRA &amp; ZAVOLOKA  -  SILENCE" width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/oKtBTDsxFVQ?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Housed in a beautiful gatefold sleeve, the release is pressed on white vinyl with the single groove looking more like a minimalistic ornament than an actual recording. You might not ever play it but it would definitely be one of the most unusual releases in any record collection.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1705010588926_76"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="678" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Kotra-Zavoloka-22Silence22-2020-vinyl-1024x678.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-350" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Kotra-Zavoloka-22Silence22-2020-vinyl-1024x678.jpeg 1024w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Kotra-Zavoloka-22Silence22-2020-vinyl-300x199.jpeg 300w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Kotra-Zavoloka-22Silence22-2020-vinyl-768x509.jpeg 768w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Kotra-Zavoloka-22Silence22-2020-vinyl.jpeg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em>Isn\u2019t it beautiful?</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There are many articles written on silence and whether it should or should not be considered music. The press release probably put it best: \u201cSILENCE IS ALWAYS HERE. SILENCE DOES NOT NEED TO BE FOUND NEITHER CREATED <em>(sic)</em>\u201d. Like white canvas, silence is the starting point, ground zero of music. This is what is there <em>before</em> the music begins.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Kvitnu was one of the most unusual labels out there and we would like to send our token of gratitude to this amazing label that now, just like that locked groove will forever be silent.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<iframe style="border: 0; width: 100%; height: 120px;" src="https://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/album=3276813495/size=large/bgcol=ffffff/linkcol=333333/tracklist=false/artwork=small/transparent=true/" seamless><a href="https://kvitnu.bandcamp.com/album/silence">Silence by Kotra &amp; Zavoloka</a></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: "<p>\ud83e\udd2b</p>\n", protected: false },
