    modified: "2024-01-11T21:21:44",
    modified_gmt: "2024-01-11T21:21:44",
    slug: "coil-musick-to-play-in-the-dark-vol-1-1999",
    status: "publish",
    type: "post",
    link: "https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/coil-musick-to-play-in-the-dark-vol-1-1999/",
    title: {
      rendered: "Coil, \u201cMusick To Play In The Dark Vol.1\u201d (1999)",
    },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>There is nothing conventional about Coil. Since its inception in the early 80s, they were the driving force in dark and occult music. Their art was a huge influence on dark ambient, goth, neofolk, dark folk and related dark-from-centre genres. Initially conceived as a solo project by John Balance (of Psychic TV) Coil evolved into a duo with the addition of Balance\u2019s partner, Peter \u201cSleazy\u201d Christopherson (of Throbbing Gristle).&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After releasing a strain of highly influential albums in the 80s and early 90s (including <em>Scatology</em> (1984), <em>Horse Rotorvator</em> (1986) and <em>Love\u2019s Secret Domain</em> (1991) the band struggled financially in the early 90s. 1999 saw their return to form with <em>Astral Disaster</em> and the first instalment in the <em>Musick To Play In The Dark</em> series.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1705008035915_76"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1007" height="500" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Coil-thevinylfactory.com_.png" alt="" class="wp-image-291" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Coil-thevinylfactory.com_.png 1007w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Coil-thevinylfactory.com_-300x149.png 300w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Coil-thevinylfactory.com_-768x381.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1007px) 100vw, 1007px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em>How my mom sees my friends \u00a9thevinylfactory.com</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Coil called this album \u201cmoon music\u201d and it combines a wide range of styles including ambient, glitch, minimalism, krautrock with some dark and twisted take on jazziness.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The production began after Coil moved into a new studio with some new equipment. Among others they used <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Optigan">Optigan</a>, an array of vintage drum machines, Roland SH-101, Synton Fenix as well as Pro Tools. John Balance originally intended to write liner notes for the release but they ended up only being published on Coil\u2019s website. In those notes, he explained the meaning behind some of the songs. \u201cAre You Shivering?\u201d refers to an MDMA trip he had when he and his friends &#8220;would ask if each other were shivering, as pure doses can make the teeth chatter and the eyesight vibrate\u201d. \u201cBroccoli\u201d is &#8220;about greens and ancestor worship\u201d and \u201cStrange Birds\u201d evokes a moment when Balance &#8220;regressed to BIRD MIND and only squawked and chirruped for three worrying days\u201d. As if anyone would&#8217;ve expected any less from Coil.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While embracing contemporary technology and adding <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Granular_synthesis">granular synthesis</a> and digital glitch effects, Balance and Christopherson still manage to retain certain warmth that was typical to their icon 80s albums.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As it is the case with many albums we are covering here, <em>Musick To Play In The Dark</em> is a world of its own and it continues to exist outside of time. This album together with the rest of Coil\u2019s output continues to inspire countless musicians looking for \u201cthe other side\u201d of the music and it will another 20 years from now.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The record was recently reissued and the new reissues look absolutely stunning! Check them out <a href="https://www.daisrecords.com/products/coil-musick-to-play-in-the-dark">here</a>. (We get no commission from this link, it\u2019s all for the musick, baby!)</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-spotify wp-block-embed-spotify wp-embed-aspect-21-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe title="Spotify Embed: Musick To Play In The Dark" style="border-radius: 12px" width="100%" height="352" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/album/7yZSVm7D1XSUnKAeRqE6FG?go=1&#038;sp_cid=4ee5ae78b0fe5b2a952220851425f3a8&#038;utm_source=oembed&#038;utm_medium=desktop"></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<iframe allow="autoplay *; encrypted-media *; fullscreen *; clipboard-write" frameborder="0" height="450" style="width:100%;max-width:660px;overflow:hidden;border-radius:10px;" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation" src="https://embed.music.apple.com/ca/album/musick-to-play-in-the-dark/1527687152"></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
