    slug: "the-knife-shaking-the-habitual-2013",
    status: "publish",
    type: "post",
    link: "https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/the-knife-shaking-the-habitual-2013/",
    title: { rendered: "The Knife, \u201cShaking The Habitual\u201d (2013)" },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>The Knife didn\u2019t bless us with quantity of their output but what we are left with is sheer quality. Their final album (hopefully to date), <em>Shaking The Habitual</em> is an indication of just how great and capable this band was.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Formed in 1999 by siblings Karin and Olof Dreijer, The Knife unleashed their self-titled debut in 2001. Although already a fully accomplished offering from the start, they achieved real fame with their sophomore <em>Deep Cuts</em>. Containing their biggest commercial hit, <a href="https://youtu.be/pPD8Ja64mRU">\u201cHeartbeats\u201d</a>\ufeff, the album was met with widespread critical acclaim and made tons of end of year and best of the decade lists. The song was covered by many acts, most notably Jos\u00e9 Gonz\u00e1lez. <a href="https://youtu.be/HxJhYpTIrl8">His version of the song</a> was even used in a BMW commercial. Despite The Knife\u2019s anti-commercial stance they agreed to the deal explaining that they needed the money to establish their own record company.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1705007906344_76"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="619" height="412" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/The-Knife-clashmusic.com_.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-286" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/The-Knife-clashmusic.com_.jpg 619w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/The-Knife-clashmusic.com_-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 619px) 100vw, 619px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em>Counting crows (hint: 2) \u00a9clashmusic.com</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Fast forward 7 years and the band unleashed their final work. <em>Shaking The Habitual</em> takes its name from a quote by French philosopher Michel Foucault. The album\u2019s themes lie in feminist and queer theory adding structuralism and environmentalism. They criticise nuclear family calling it &#8220;an institution that conserves inequality, injustice and exclusion\u201d. They believe &#8220;in solidarity beyond nuclear families, nations and economical unions\u201d. <a href="https://pitchfork.com/features/interview/9092-the-knife/">When talking to Pitchfork</a> Karin said that &#8220;people would be happier sharing things and being much more of a collective rather than working from these neo-liberal ideas of just looking after yourself.\u201d&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Such strong political stance is nothing new for The Knife. After winning the Swedish Grammis, the duo boycotted the ceremony and send members of <a href="https://www.guerrillagirls.com/">Guerrilla Girls</a> with number 50 written on their costumes as a protest against male dominance in the music industry.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1705007906344_95"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="683" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/fever-ray-redbull.com_-1024x683.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-287" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/fever-ray-redbull.com_-1024x683.jpeg 1024w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/fever-ray-redbull.com_-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/fever-ray-redbull.com_-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/fever-ray-redbull.com_.jpeg 1500w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em>Karin Dreijer performing as Fever Ray \u00a9redbull.com</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the greatest things about The Knife is that they\u2019ve always had incredible music to support their ideas. On <em>Shaking The Habitual</em> their abilities are on full display. In over one hour of music they go from their signature beat-driven electronica featuring Karin\u2019s instantly recognisable vocals to quite aggressive industrial-infused tracks to barely intelligible ambient that at low volumes might be confused with the sound of your actual ambience. Those mood swings are what makes this album so great. It is so omnivorous that you won\u2019t stop marvelling at Karin and Olof\u2019s abilities.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It\u2019s also kind of sad considering this was their final offering. Hopefully to date.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-spotify wp-block-embed-spotify wp-embed-aspect-21-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe title="Spotify Embed: Shaking The Habitual" style="border-radius: 12px" width="100%" height="352" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/album/6GWQ6fq8krujlglglMPyPu?go=1&#038;sp_cid=4ee5ae78b0fe5b2a952220851425f3a8&#038;utm_source=oembed&#038;utm_medium=desktop"></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<iframe allow="autoplay *; encrypted-media *; fullscreen *; clipboard-write" frameborder="0" height="450" style="width:100%;max-width:660px;overflow:hidden;border-radius:10px;" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation" src="https://embed.music.apple.com/us/album/shaking-the-habitual/1489761397"></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
