    modified_gmt: "2024-01-11T20:41:56",
    slug: "various-artists-wayfaring-strangers-cosmic-american-music-2016",
    status: "publish",
    type: "post",
    link: "https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/various-artists-wayfaring-strangers-cosmic-american-music-2016/",
    title: {
      rendered:
        "Various Artists, \u201cWayfaring Strangers: Cosmic American Music\u201d (2016)",
    },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>This installment in Numero Group\u2019s <em>Wayfaring Strangers</em> series is an exquisite selection of privately pressed country from the early 70s.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But it\u2019s not <em>that</em> kind of country. The music compiled here mixes psychedelia with pedal steel. It is perhaps the perfect music equivalent of the famous <a href="https://i.pinimg.com/originals/d2/44/ba/d244bacb7ce121063f49ef110d66f39d.jpg">Gram Parsons\u2019 nudie suit</a>: it\u2019s technically country but with a druggy twist. GP\u2019s influence is actually all over the comp. His quote is on the hype sticker and it perfectly sums up his vision and the main idea behind the whole \u201cCosmic American Music\u201d thing: \u201cIt\u2019s basically a Southern soul group playing country and gospel-oriented music with a steel guitar\u201d.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By the end of the 60s musicians were becoming weary of pushing the boundaries and exploring \u201cspace\u201d. So they turned their interest towards their \u201croots\u201d. Over the course of several years The Byrds, The Band, Dylan and Grateful Dead all began to implement simpler music forms and non-rock instruments. All those outdated banjos, fiddles and pedal steels suddenly were \u201cin\u201d again. Few years on and country-rock became a prominent force in music. Much to Parsons\u2019 disdain. He felt his ideas were misunderstood and called country-rock a \u201cplastic dry-fuck\u201d. We\u2019re going to save the debate about country-rock\u2019s merit for a later date and focus on the artists <em>Wayfaring Strangers\u2026 </em>highlights.&nbsp;Those early followers of Gram Parsons\u2019 vision were so inspired by him that they made all those great privately pressed recordings that the general folk totally forgotten about.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The best part of this compilation is that without major labels worrying about commercial viability and dictating the sound, these artists were virtually free to explore whatever the fuck they wanted. And it shows here big time. The general countryness is mixed with rock\u2019n\u2019roll, jazz-rock, psychedelia (duh) and sheer pure unconfined weirdness. Sometimes it\u2019s hard to believe that the songs were recorded almost 50 years ago (cheeeeeesy). Not only some of them would sound perfectly in place today but also the influence of that short period seems to be resonating with quite a few artists in 2020. All of those factors plus of course the obscurity factor are what make <em>Cosmic American Music</em> so appealing. If you\u2019re not a fan of country music this compilation would be a perfect way to ease in. And if you hate it so much you don\u2019t want anything to do with country, you\u2019ll still find this comp enjoyable.&nbsp;Promise.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And a bonus super random but super cool (in our opinion) fact: Don Dixon, the singer of the band Arrogance featured here actually produced R.E.M.\u2019s first two albums. Cool, huh?</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-spotify wp-block-embed-spotify wp-embed-aspect-21-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe title="Spotify Embed: Wayfaring Strangers: Cosmic American Music" style="border-radius: 12px" width="100%" height="352" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/album/5uFF8Q8WlrvtK2WfK9VupC?go=1&#038;sp_cid=4ee5ae78b0fe5b2a952220851425f3a8&#038;utm_source=oembed&#038;utm_medium=desktop"></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<iframe allow="autoplay *; encrypted-media *; fullscreen *; clipboard-write" frameborder="0" height="450" style="width:100%;max-width:660px;overflow:hidden;border-radius:10px;" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation" src="https://embed.music.apple.com/ca/album/wayfaring-strangers-cosmic-american-music/1085766331"></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: {
      rendered:
        "<p>Psychedelia-laden country for those who want to explore space while grabbing onto their roots</p>\n",
      protected: false,
    },
