    title: { rendered: "Helena Hauff, \u201cQualm\u201d (2018)" },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>German DJ and producer delivers one of the greatest electronic releases of the past decade. Based in Hamburg, Helena Hauff started making waves a few years ago. She hosted her own night, Birds and Other Instruments in Hamburg\u2019s The Golden Pudel club. In 2013 she released her debut EP, <em>Action Reactio</em> and has been continuously ascending ever since. Her recent <a href="https://shop.tresorberlin.com/index.php/kern005bundle.html">mix for Berlin\u2019s legendary Tresor club</a> confirms that she shows no signs of slowing down.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It feels great that an artist like Hauff gets all the recognition. Her sets scavenge dark and dirty corners of techno, industrial, electro and EBM. She knows how to throw in pure sonic grime and do that with taste. No wonder her set was named BBC Radio 1\u2019s Essential Mix of the year (the first female ever to earn the accolade).\u00a0</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio embed-youtube"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe loading="lazy" title="Helena Hauff Boiler Room x Dekmantel Festival DJ Set" width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/OdJy_g1G7Ho?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When putting <em>Qualm</em> on for the first time an unsuspecting listener might think that their speakers are busted. Even more so, during <a href="https://www.xlr8r.com/front-page/ask-the-experts-helena-hauff">a Q&amp;A session for XLR8R</a> Hauff herself admitted that once at a festival in Hamburg a guy screamed at her: \u201cCan\u2019t you hear how fucking shit all your bass drums sound?\u201d.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1705005149849_81"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="725" height="483" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/helena-hauff-fact-magazine.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-224" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/helena-hauff-fact-magazine.jpg 725w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/helena-hauff-fact-magazine-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 725px) 100vw, 725px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em>Her kicks will kick the shit out of you \u00a9 FACT Magazine</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But isn\u2019t \u201cshit\u201d the whole point though? It definitely is on <em>Qualm</em>. Every single one of the 12 tracks here is packed with overdriven overloaded analog magic. The album is indeed produced using only analog equipment. Actually just one synthesizer and one drum machine.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Musically, Helena Hauff hits all the right spots. <em>Qualm</em> mixes techno, acid, IDM, coldwave while adding distorted and twisted soundscapes. Despite pushing the levels into red, the album retains a certain \u201cpop\u201d appeal and sounds weirdly romantic at times. Some tracks (like the opener \u201cBarrow Boot Boys\u201d) consist of just the drum machine. Grimy kicks, claps and snares create a primal feel while not lacking anything at all. There\u2019s no melody here but who even needs it? The drums provide everything. <em>Qualm</em> channels primal music through a prism of various shades of dark and twisted. It\u2019s radical as it is mesmerizing.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-spotify wp-block-embed-spotify wp-embed-aspect-21-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe title="Spotify Embed: Qualm" style="border-radius: 12px" width="100%" height="352" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/album/2hYmcjIinZoVCog5sP4k0H?go=1&#038;sp_cid=4ee5ae78b0fe5b2a952220851425f3a8&#038;utm_source=oembed&#038;utm_medium=desktop"></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<iframe allow="autoplay *; encrypted-media *; fullscreen *; clipboard-write" frameborder="0" height="450" style="width:100%;max-width:660px;overflow:hidden;border-radius:10px;" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation" src="https://embed.music.apple.com/ca/album/qualm/1389701413"></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: {
      rendered:
        "<p>Noisy primal electronica from the queen of glorified dirt</p>\n",
      protected: false,
    },
