    id: 217,
    date: "2024-01-11T20:24:24",
    date_gmt: "2024-01-11T20:24:24",
    guid: { rendered: "http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/?p=217" },
    modified: "2024-01-11T20:24:24",
    modified_gmt: "2024-01-11T20:24:24",
    slug: "clap-clap-tayi-bebba-2014",
    status: "publish",
    type: "post",
    link: "https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/clap-clap-tayi-bebba-2014/",
    title: { rendered: "Clap! Clap!, \u201cTayi Bebba\u201d (2014)" },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>This is one of those perfect albums where every single note counts. The very first splashes of percussion (kinda reminiscent of Can\u2019s \u201cFuture Days\u201d) indicate something great to come and every single track on this album is simply amazing. It\u2019s an astonishing whirlwind of syncopated percussion, field recordings, some very deep bass and electronic touches. Oh and other sounds like splashes of water or neighing horses.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Released in 2014, <em>Tayi Bebba </em>immediately found its fanbase. Okay Africa named it one of the best albums of 2014, it was on <a href="http://bleep.com/">bleep.com</a>\u2019s \u201cEnd Of Year Roundup 2014\u201d and the track \u201cViarejo\u201d ended up on the Grand Theft Auto V soundtrack.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Clap! Clap! is an alias of Italian producer Digi G&#8217;Alessio who\u2019s also a long-time jazz musician. After releasing a handful of well-received EPs as Clap! Clap! in 2013-2014, he went all-in and released <em>Tayi Bebba</em>, a conceptual 17-track workout in African rhythms, UK bass, Chicago footwork, Hip-Hop and contemporary electronic music. The album moves between those styles seamlessly incorporating something new into each next track. \u201cHoly Cave\u201d mixes beautifully sung peaceful melody with some nice deep bass, \u201cAshiko\u201d progresses from 80s style groove into a destructive and menacing bass track and \u201cConqueror\u201d goes from tribal percussion to lush electronica to some more gorgeous bass production.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1705004604364_76"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="575" height="435" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/clap-clap.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-219" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/clap-clap.jpeg 575w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/clap-clap-300x227.jpeg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 575px) 100vw, 575px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em>Those fields won\u2019t record themselves</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Tayi Bebba</em> also acts as a tour of an imaginary island with every next track marking a new location, ritual or event. All these from a coherent story of how Tayiians fought agains invaders. You can find full story <a href="http://www.tayibebba.com/">here</a> but just FYI the track \u201cBurbuka&#8221; stands for a blend made from the herbs of Jzimpo Mima and \u201cKwasi\u201d is the son of the legendary Opete and whose magic powers are linked to the four elements: earth, air, fire and water.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Each single track on this album is full of energy, life and space. <em>Tayi Bebba</em> was highly praised by Paul Simon, for whom Clap! Clap! produced three tracks on critically acclaimed <em>Stranger To Stranger</em>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This album covers so much musical ground that pretty much everyone can find something they like about it. 6 years after its release it sounds as fresh as ever.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-spotify wp-block-embed-spotify wp-embed-aspect-21-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe title="Spotify Embed: Tayi Bebba" style="border-radius: 12px" width="100%" height="352" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/album/47GRUjIo1RbZNxFkNoPk9z?go=1&#038;sp_cid=4ee5ae78b0fe5b2a952220851425f3a8&#038;utm_source=oembed&#038;utm_medium=desktop"></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<iframe allow="autoplay *; encrypted-media *; fullscreen *; clipboard-write" frameborder="0" height="450" style="width:100%;max-width:660px;overflow:hidden;border-radius:10px;" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation" src="https://embed.music.apple.com/ca/album/tayi-bebba/1518971120"></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: {
      rendered: "<p>Full on assault of percussion-driven bass music</p>\n",
      protected: false,
    },
