    id: 197,
    date: "2024-01-11T20:07:52",
    date_gmt: "2024-01-11T20:07:52",
    guid: { rendered: "http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/?p=197" },
    modified: "2024-01-11T20:07:52",
    modified_gmt: "2024-01-11T20:07:52",
    slug: "girls-album-2009",
    status: "publish",
    type: "post",
    link: "https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/girls-album-2009/",
    title: { rendered: "Girls, \u201cAlbum\u201d (2009)" },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>I still remember how a friend of mine showed me the video for \u201cLust for Life\u201d (the NSFW version) and I just could not believe my eyes. Not only was the song a rapid two-minute embodiment of everything I was looking for in music at the time but it also perfectly captured the life I was living when I was 16. To this day when I hear the neurotic strumming of \u201cLust for Life\u201d it makes me wanna jump on my bed with a bong in one hand and a bottle of vodka in the other.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The music throughout the album is heavily soaked with nostalgia. You get fashionable indie rock, folk, 50s girl group drum beats, lo-fi dirt and god knows what else. The production is supposed to be lo-fi and you can hear some production artifacts but all the soft pillowy dirt only adds to the album\u2019s glory. The band was compared to Beach Boys too many times but rightfully so. Girls do have the same bright sunny colors that early Beach Boys had.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1705003561736_72"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="960" height="540" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/girls.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-199" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/girls.jpg 960w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/girls-300x169.jpg 300w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/girls-768x432.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em>Boys \u00a9StyleCaster</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The story behind the band is pretty sad though. The lead singer Christopher Owens was born in the Children of God cult, his older brother died of pneumonia because the cult didn\u2019t believe in medical help, his father left, and his mom was forced to do sex work. And even though the songs on the album are mostly pop takes on girls and breakups, Owens\u2019 voice has some quality of a damaged person to it. Maybe it\u2019s far-fetched but it\u2019s quite fitting to believe that it isn\u2019t.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>At the time of its release the album was praised by almost everyone. Some of the album\u2019s numbers may sound outdated today but it\u2019s only because we grew weary of jangling sunshine chords of 00s indie. There is nothing <em>actually</em> outdated about the music and it won\u2019t reach its expiration date any time soon. It is still great for parties, campfires or lonely nights after a breakup.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It\u2019s been 11 years since the album\u2019s release and \u201cMorning Light\u201d and \u201cLust for Life\u201d are still in my favorite music playlists. I would occasionally turn the volume up on \u201cLust for Life\u201d when getting ready for a party and even in the middle of winter the song would make everything sunny and warm.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-spotify wp-block-embed-spotify wp-embed-aspect-21-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe title="Spotify Embed: Album" style="border-radius: 12px" width="100%" height="352" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/album/2d2nOfrJxU2Wpzc1AAZewC?go=1&#038;sp_cid=4ee5ae78b0fe5b2a952220851425f3a8&#038;utm_source=oembed&#038;utm_medium=desktop"></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<iframe allow="autoplay *; encrypted-media *; fullscreen *; clipboard-write" frameborder="0" height="450" style="width:100%;max-width:660px;overflow:hidden;border-radius:10px;" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation" src="https://embed.music.apple.com/us/album/album/1699649591"></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: "<p>The sweet 16 anthem</p>\n", protected: false },
