    slug: "william-basinski-the-disintegration-loops-2002",
    status: "publish",
    type: "post",
    link: "https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/william-basinski-the-disintegration-loops-2002/",
    title: {
      rendered: "William Basinski, \u201cThe Disintegration Loops\u201d (2002)",
    },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>Even without the backstory \u201cThe Disintegration Loops\u201d is a compelling and satisfying listen. The melancholic and detached sounds that slowly decay overtime evoke the very essence of burning melancholy they were meant to. But it\u2019s the backstory that turns this great album into a masterpiece.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1705002925398_76"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="750" height="450" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/basinski.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-180" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/basinski.jpg 750w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/basinski-300x180.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em><s>Mickey Rourke</s></em> \u00a9Shakti Music</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The record started out back in 1982 as recordings of found sound sources, shortwave radio and delay systems. Years later, as Basinski decided to transfer the records onto digital carriers he noticed that the tape deteriorated over time and each time it played it would lose some ferrite thus losing fidelity. The resulting music gradually goes from something to nothing literally disintegrating in front of the listener.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Basisnki finished the project the morning of the 9/11 attacks and sat on the roof of his apartment building watching the towers collapse. He made a video that day and used the stills from it as cover art. The next morning he played the \u201cDisintegration Loop 1.1\u201d as a soundtrack to the aftermath.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It\u2019s hard to find anything that would express the horrible event as powerfully as this music does. The deterioration of the tape creates a sense of existential despair. Basinski is using much more than the sound itself to create a piece of art. The music transcends mere entertainment into a statement. It\u2019s our own disintegration showing through the quiet crackling.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-spotify wp-block-embed-spotify wp-embed-aspect-21-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe title="Spotify Embed: The Disintegration Loops (Remastered)" style="border-radius: 12px" width="100%" height="352" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/album/1xVP4eFcagXNtQMvEXfyeV?go=1&#038;sp_cid=4ee5ae78b0fe5b2a952220851425f3a8&#038;utm_source=oembed&#038;utm_medium=desktop"></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<iframe allow="autoplay *; encrypted-media *; fullscreen *; clipboard-write" frameborder="0" height="450" style="width:100%;max-width:660px;overflow:hidden;border-radius:10px;" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation" src="https://embed.music.apple.com/ca/album/the-disintegration-loops-remastered/908005350"></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: {
      rendered: "<p>Music is more than what you hear</p>\n",
      protected: false,
    },
