    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>Calling this album \u201ca comprehensive guide\u201d is no mere exaggeration: with 49 tracks divided into 7 discs, 7 tracks each (hence \u201c7G\u201d) this record covers A LOT of ground.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Conceptually, each disc is dedicated to a separate instrument: <em>Drums, Guitar, </em><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roland_JP-8000#Supersaw"><em>Supersaw</em></a><em> </em>(sound of multiple detuned sawtooth oscillators),<em> Piano, Nord, Spoken Word </em>and <em>Extreme Vocals</em>. Over the course of 49 tracks, A.G. Cook also covers Blur, Charli XCX, Taylor Swift, Sia, The Strokes, Smashing Pumpkins and more.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Releasing (or even conceiving) a project of such grandeur may seem self-indulgent, but A. G. Cook is not a mere mortal artist. For the past 7 years he\u2019s been the head of PC Music, perhaps one of the most unusual and forward-thinking electronic music labels in the world today. You absolutely must <a href="https://pcmusic.bandcamp.com/">check them out</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Apart from being quite busy with the label, A. G. Cook is probably most-well know as an executive producer of the last several Charli XCX albums. He also made an appearance in her stunning, self-directed <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mPRy1B4t5YA">\u201cBoys\u201d music video</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1705002569313_76"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="720" height="720" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/a.g.cook-paradigm-talent-agency.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-176" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/a.g.cook-paradigm-talent-agency.jpg 720w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/a.g.cook-paradigm-talent-agency-300x300.jpg 300w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/a.g.cook-paradigm-talent-agency-150x150.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em>Cillian Murphy, anyone? \u00a9Paradigm Talent Agency</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Cook\u2019s main influences (that drip into the output of the whole label) lie in various incarnations of bubblegum music with a certain degree of abrasiveness: 90s europop, hardcore and happy hardcore, nightcore and bubblegum pop itself. But 7G is far more than just that. \u201cA-Z\u201d is a high octane jungle-infused take, \u201cBeetlebum\u201d is a perfect mix of guitar-based indie with dirrrrrty beats, \u201cNote Velocity\u201d could\u2019ve been written by a mid-20th century experimental composer and \u201cNo Yeah\u201d is ASMR af.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201c7G\u201d can be viewed as a window into Cook\u2019s mind. Some of the riffs have been used in other tracks, some tracks sound more like sketches rather than finished songs and some feel like lab experiments. But there is nothing half-baked about the music. A. G. Cook\u2019s dedication and meticulousness are just uncanny. After all, he made a <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VwH1sFJYzPA">note-by-note cover of \u201cWindowlicker\u201d</a>, who the fuck even does that?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>He can really do anything, which is being showcased in full here. Guitar songs? Check. Abstract soundscapes? Check. Sugary soda-water-cotton-candy-bubblegum electronica? Big check. Outright bizarre stuff? Check.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Covers deserve an honorable mention here. While the covers seem to get some shit online they are far from being bad or lazy. It just seems that when tackling anthemic classics like \u201cBeetlebum\u201d, \u201cToday\u201d or \u201cChandelier\u201d you can never win. And let\u2019s be honest, Cook\u2019s take on these timeless songs is not particularly what you\u2019d expect.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you could only choose one album to exemplify what electronic music is in 2020, \u201c7G\u201d should certainly go to the desert island with you.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-spotify wp-block-embed-spotify wp-embed-aspect-21-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe title="Spotify Embed: 7G" style="border-radius: 12px" width="100%" height="352" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/album/0PHVIdlkceOpjYgvUER4Nd?go=1&#038;sp_cid=4ee5ae78b0fe5b2a952220851425f3a8&#038;utm_source=oembed&#038;utm_medium=desktop"></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<iframe allow="autoplay *; encrypted-media *; fullscreen *; clipboard-write" frameborder="0" height="450" style="width:100%;max-width:660px;overflow:hidden;border-radius:10px;" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation" src="https://embed.music.apple.com/us/album/7g/1544377328"></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
