    slug: "kate-bush-the-dreaming-1982",
    status: "publish",
    type: "post",
    link: "https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/kate-bush-the-dreaming-1982/",
    title: { rendered: "Kate Bush, \u201cThe Dreaming\u201d (1982)" },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>Yes, Kate Bush is by no means an obscure artist. But it doesn\u2019t make her less weird and The Dreaming any less unconventional and exciting. She was dismantling pop music and putting the pieces together the way she saw fit. This album is unmistakably pop but put together through experimental and avant-garde.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Legend has it that Bush arrived to EMI with a collection of songs from which her first four albums were made up. \u201cThe Dreaming\u201d was her first effort of newly written material. Having worked with a producer before, Bush decided to produce this album herself. Armed with a relatively new and unexplored Fairlight CMI synth and a Lynn drum machine Bush set out to create something completely from scratch. Coupled with idiosyncratic songwriting and absolutely insane vocal work the music creates a rich experience and sensory overload. A plethora of folk instruments, shifting time signatures, synthesizer textures, vocal loops and polyrhythms are all a bold statement of an artist brave enough to go beyond the conventional. She creates rich soundscapes practically unheard of in 80s pop.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1704997855770_76"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="749" height="743" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Kate-Bush.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-140" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Kate-Bush.jpg 749w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Kate-Bush-300x298.jpg 300w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Kate-Bush-150x150.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 749px) 100vw, 749px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em>Kate Bush and a bush (hahaha, hee hee hee, haw haw haw) \u00a9The Internet</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Her vocals alone would be a work of art even without the palette of musical background they enjoy here. Bush comes up a plethora of vocal sounds and techniques pushing the boundaries of what a pop vocalist is allowed to do.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The lyrics draw on a vast number of influences from old crime films and the Vietnam war to the plight of Indigenous Australians and life and death of Harry Houdini.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Upon its release the album quickly became a fan favorite but was considered a commercial failure for an artist her size. It was truly appreciated only years later. Almost four decades after it was released its landmark status is still standing strong. Bjork and Big Boi name this album among their favorites. Kate Bush herself called \u201cThe Dreaming\u201d her \u201cmad\u201d album. Even though \u201cThe Dreaming\u201d was overwhelmingly called \u201cuncommercial\u201d it went straight to #3 in UK chart. This fact was mocked by Bush herself who stated in an interview that it seemed ironic to her that the album everyone called \u201cuncommercial\u201d performed that well in the charts.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The album is a work of an artist finally getting to know herself and setting herself free from the boundaries of pop music. Kate Bush went on to become a true legend who sustained a long and successful carrier but this album is where the genius was being born and it makes the listening even more exciting.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-spotify wp-block-embed-spotify wp-embed-aspect-21-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe title="Spotify Embed: The Dreaming (2018 Remaster)" style="border-radius: 12px" width="100%" height="352" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/album/59dmyw7CgPluQ6PlTmn7ik?go=1&#038;sp_cid=4ee5ae78b0fe5b2a952220851425f3a8&#038;utm_source=oembed&#038;utm_medium=desktop"></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<iframe allow="autoplay *; encrypted-media *; fullscreen *; clipboard-write" frameborder="0" height="450" style="width:100%;max-width:660px;overflow:hidden;border-radius:10px;" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation" src="https://embed.music.apple.com/us/album/the-dreaming/1675374915"></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: {
      rendered:
        "<p>With \u201cThe Dreaming\u201d Kate Bush turned from a star into an artist</p>\n",
      protected: false,
    },
