    modified: "2024-01-11T18:29:48",
    modified_gmt: "2024-01-11T18:29:48",
    slug: "grinderman-grinderman-2007",
    status: "publish",
    type: "post",
    link: "https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/grinderman-grinderman-2007/",
    title: { rendered: "Grinderman, \u201cGrinderman\u201d (2007)" },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>Nick Cave has always been an oddball. His signature blend of no wave, gothic, blues and pop is not something a lot of artists can pull off. With a career spanning god knows how many decades, his catalogue jumps through so many genres it\u2019s easier to just tag it as \u201cNick Cave\u201d.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Grinderman is not particularly a hidden gem being Nick Cave\u2019s project but it feels a bit overlooked compared to his other work with The Birthday Party or The Bad Seeds.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Nick Cave started writing songs for this project on guitar, the instrument he could barely play and it certainly added to the primal nature of the sound. The music is gritty and dirty but retains it\u2019s pop sensibility which is sort of a tag line for lots of his songs. &nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-full post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1704997716726_76"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="300" height="300" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/grinderman.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-136" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/grinderman.jpg 300w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/grinderman-150x150.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em>Dat mustache tho \u00a9The Quietus</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The album starts with an amphetamine of a song \u201cGet It On\u201d and the speed never really goes away.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201cNo Pussy Blues\u201d is an absolutely hilarious lament to the days of bygone good looks and being hard but not getting laid. As mentioned by Pitchfork, \u201cNo Pussy Blues\u201d only gets funnier as you age. Will check back in a few decades.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201c(I Don\u2019t Need You To) Set Me Free)\u201d is slow bluesy garage rock, \u201cHoney Bee (Let\u2019s Fly To Mars)\u201d feels like it was written on speed and actually features Nick Cave doing the \u201cbzzz\u201d sound with lots of attitude and \u201cGo Tell The Women\u201d is either mocking or glorifying misogyny (although Cave\u2019s own words indicate he meant the first).&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It\u2019s impossible to pick highlights on this record, every song is a highlight.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Raw, dirty, primal but at the same time smart and melodic, this is a truly omnivorous record.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-spotify wp-block-embed-spotify wp-embed-aspect-21-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe title="Spotify Embed: Grinderman" style="border-radius: 12px" width="100%" height="352" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/album/7H8mwwZrY0wptuWiIln2pp?go=1&#038;sp_cid=4ee5ae78b0fe5b2a952220851425f3a8&#038;utm_source=oembed&#038;utm_medium=desktop"></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<iframe allow="autoplay *; encrypted-media *; fullscreen *; clipboard-write" frameborder="0" height="450" style="width:100%;max-width:660px;overflow:hidden;border-radius:10px;" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation" src="https://embed.music.apple.com/us/album/grinderman/1710206295"></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
