    id: 77,
    date: "2023-12-07T19:08:02",
    date_gmt: "2023-12-07T19:08:02",
    guid: { rendered: "http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/?p=77" },
    modified: "2024-01-10T16:16:31",
    modified_gmt: "2024-01-10T16:16:31",
    slug: "holly-herndon-proto-2019",
    status: "publish",
    type: "post",
    link: "https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/holly-herndon-proto-2019/",
    title: { rendered: "Holly Herndon, &#8220;PROTO&#8221; (2019)" },
    content: {
      rendered:
        '\n<p>Unlike a huge chunk of contemporary electronic music (or pop music in general) Holly Herndon is not just a musician but an actual scientist. Born and raised in Tennessee and based in Berlin, Herndon studied composition at Stanford and completed her PhD at Stanford\u2019s Center for Computer Research in Music and Acoustics (wow). She also teaches, holds lectures performs workshops and builds her own instruments using Max/MSP.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For this album, Herndon created an AI program with her partner Mathew Dryhurst and programmer Jules LaPlace. They named the AI \u201cSpawn\u201d and together with contributing vocalists taught her to sing. Spawn, to which Herndon refers to as \u201cshe\u201d is considered to be an ensemble member rather than a mere program. The idea behind it was to try and make AI less dehumanizing (cooooool).&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-image alignright post-content-image" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1700667854618_76"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="800" height="800" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress-trunk/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/image.jpeg" alt="Her last name is also a tongue twister \u00a9BOMB Magazine" class="wp-image-78" srcset="https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/image.jpeg 800w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/image-300x300.jpeg 300w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/image-150x150.jpeg 150w, https://qfn.fuu.mybluehost.me/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/image-768x768.jpeg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em>Her last name is also a tongue twister \u00a9BOMB Magazine</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Fittingly enough, the album does sound really human. Like a computer-based person. Musically, it builds on centuries of vocal music drawing from such influences as Appalachian Sacred Harp Singing (\u201cFrontier\u201d) and Irish Chants. Quite remote from computers, isn\u2019t it? But it still retains characteristics of contemporary electronic music and was created almost entirely using computers.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While having an actual computer program as one of the musicians a lot of the album\u2019s sounds are actually human-based which somehow reassures that AI is still created by humans and we are connected and in control (for now). On the other hand it might give you chills as you realize that it is a <em>being</em> created by humans from nothing which is potentially far superior than we are.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some Bandcamp users said this album was close to a religious experience, a point that is indeed quite relatable.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>No matter what your personal stance on AI is, \u201cPROTO\u201d is not only curious from a scientific standpoint, it\u2019s an incredible and compelling listen on its own. Holly Herndon is a master of electronic music and a true innovator. Easily one the best electronic albums&nbsp; of 2019</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-spotify wp-block-embed-spotify wp-embed-aspect-21-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">\n<iframe title="Spotify Embed: PROTO" style="border-radius: 12px" width="100%" height="352" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen allow="autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" loading="lazy" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/album/3PkYFFSJTPxOhnSYBtyZsk?si=E0_AV_DJR7KTmT8UHlZFfg&#038;utm_source=oembed"></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<iframe allow="autoplay *; encrypted-media *;" frameborder="0" height="450" style="width:100%;overflow:hidden;background:transparent;" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-storage-access-by-user-activation allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation" src="https://embed.music.apple.com/ca/album/proto/1454113472"></iframe>\n',
      protected: false,
    },
    excerpt: { rendered: "<p>AI-assisted electronica</p>\n", protected: false },
